summary: U.S. Safety sets the standard for comfort and compatibility with Comfort-Air™ series respirators. Molded from pure silicone, the wide interior flange, deep chin cup and rolled edges of the Comfort-Air™ mask make it the “hands down” favorite for long-term comfort and fit. The textured no-slip face seal and swivel retainers ensure proper placement. Extra large inhalation valve, unique corrugated exhale valve and minimized “dead air” space provide low breathing resistance and added comfort. Patented multi-position cartridge placement and low-fitting mask design allow maximum compatibility with other PPE. NIOSH approved.

meta_description: Lightweight and ultra-low profile, the Diskit™ revolutionizes comfort and compatibility.
description: Lightweight and ultra-low profile, the Diskit™ revolutionizes comfort and compatibility.
short_description: Lightweight - only 0.8 oz. Ultra-low profile Crush-proof internal frame Low breathing resistance Multi-position connector Extended filter life* Available welding spark shield Rigid Internal Frame Offset Filter Connection Diskit Cartridge Construction
summary: Light weight and ultra low-profile, the Diskit™ P100 Filter from U.S. Safety revolutionizes wearer comfort and compatibility with other PPE. The offset connector allows the filter to be positioned three different ways on the mask to maximize wearer visibility as well as compatibility with other PPE, such as safety glasses, goggles, face shields and welding helmets. Only 5/8 “ thick, the Diskit™ weighs just 0.8 oz, yet the rigid internal frame prevents crushing and extends filter life. Patented space plenums allow the filter media to evenly “load” to the edge, resulting in noticeably lower breathing resistance compared to standard filters. Diskit™ is compatible with U.S. Safety Comfort-Air™ and Comfort-Ease™ Respirators. Welding Application: Patented spark shield protects the filter from sparks and welding splatter.
size_info: P100 particulate filter, minimum 99.97% efficient protection against oil & non-oil particulates (10 pr/box, case qty: 10)

short_description: Flip-Up IR Shade Lens Adjustable Nosepiece High Impact Protection Rx Capable Blocks Harmful IR* and UV
summary: nfraSpec™ offers the ultimate versatility for protection against IR hazards. The flip-down IR filter lens can be deployed instantly when you need it, without the need to change eyewear. Clear lenses provide high-impact protection at all times. Prescription lenses can be installed for the ultimate in convenience for Rx wearers. InfraSpec™ reduces the risk of eye injury from impact by combining optional IR protection and impact protection in a single design with all-day comfort. *Infrared (IR) protection only provide when shaded IR filter lens is in the down position. Exposure to high levels of infrared radiation without proper eye protection has been linked to the development of various forms of permanent damage to the eye, including cataracts. Consult OSHA Standards to select the appropriate IR shade according to the hazard/application.

description: Light weight and ultra low-profile, the Diskit® P100 Filter from Dentec Safety revolutionizes wearer comfort and compatibility with other PPE. The offset connector allows the filter to be positioned three different ways on the mask to maximize wearer visibility as well as compatibility with other PPE, such as safety glasses, goggles, face shields and welding helmets. Only 5/8" thick, the Diskit® weighs just 0.8 oz, yet the rigid internal frame prevents crushing and extends filter life. Patented space plenums allow the filter media to evenly "load" to the edge, resulting in noticeably lower breathing resistance ompared to standard filters. Diskit® is compatible with Dentec Safety Comfort-Air® and Comfort-Ease™ Respirators.
summary: P100 particulate filter minimum 99.97% efficient protection against oil & non-oil particulates  (10 pr/box).
